gov.cms.qrda.validator.model

Class Failure

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.cms.qrda.validator.model.Failure
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Failure
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The Failure class represents a failure generated when a test XML file is validated against a given schematron. A Failure is considered 'critical' if the failure is generated due to an "error" assertion failing: A SHALL assertion fails A Failure is considered non-critical if the failure is generated due to a "warning" assertion failing. A SHOULD/MAY assertion fails The id, location, test and statement instance variables in a Failure object are copies of data elements in the test XML file that was validated.
    Author:
    Dan Donahue, Michael Holck ESAC Inc.
